On my 64th birthday last year, my husband brought me a cup of tea in bed to the strains of 'When I'm 64' from his iPod, and we sang along in the cheesiest of ways and laughed at ourselves - but at 64 you're no longer worried about embarrassing yourself, especially when you're both still healthy and enjoying life together. Not trying to crow (we've had some dreadful and extremely challenging times) but please realise IT'S JUST A SONG (I believe 'Yesterday' was originally going to be called 'Scrambled Eggs' - that's how serious Lennon and McCartney were). By the way, I also adore Bob Dylan and Leonard Cohen for their songs, not necessarily for their great messages.



