Author::::NoSuddenMovements
DateTime::::2016-03-09T09:01:49Z
McCartney wrote it when he was young before the Beatles. It's a theme that he returned to several times. It isn't difficult to notice that McCartney was one of the foremost composers of our time and that his work always explores the same few themes. In a later song he sings "Here we sit, two lonely old people". The song Your Mother Should Know falls obliquely into this category as does Uncle Albert and even Backseat of My Car. It's explorations of how love grows and changes with age and often they are paeons to old age, McCartney seemed to have great respect for his elders, one of the most interesting driving forces on the Beatles' music. A lesser theme is technology because they lived through the time when telephones and TVs gradually reached the working classes. So you can find several songs based around calling someone on the phone and even Lennon wrote songs about how you would have to go and knock on a girl's door rather than calling. McCartney plays with the idea on the song Give Me a Ring.



